  "notes": "App lives at apps/stanford_school/ with prefix /school and storage at storage/stanford_school.sqlite3 (WAL + foreign keys). Static files mount at /stanford_school-static. Routers split by domain: routers/admissions.py, routers/students.py, routers/attendance.py, routers/exams.py, routers/grades.py, routers/fees.py, routers/transport.py, routers/library.py, routers/parents.py, routers/ai.py, routers/voice.py. Services mirror routers: services/admissions.py, services/students.py, services/attendance.py, services/exams.py, services/grades.py, services/fees.py, services/transport.py, services/library.py, services/parents.py, services/ai.py, services/voice.py, services/demo.py. AI service uses shared.ai.ask_ai with school-specific system prompts requesting JSON output; _extract_json() parses robustly. AI insights are persisted to ai_insight table and saved to omni-brain under namespace=stanford_school. Voice transcription uses faster-whisper via services/voice.py with stt_corrector for school terminology (subject names, grade labels). Parent portal tabs are read-only views secured by parent_id linkage. Fee bulk generation creates one record per student in a grade for a given fee_type and academic_year. Library fine calculation: 1 unit per day overdue, configurable in config.py. Admission-to-enrollment flow: POST /api/admissions/{id}/enroll creates student record from approved admission data and marks admission status as 'enrolled'. Dashboard stats endpoint aggregates across all tables for admin/principal summary view. Omni launcher tile: <div class='nav-row' onclick=\"window.open('/school','_blank')\" style='cursor:pointer'><span>🏫</span>Stanford International School</div>. All routes return {ok: true, ...} on success or raise HTTPException. Pydantic request models defined per router. Demo seed data in services/demo.py creates 5 students, 2 parents, 1 transport route, 5 library books for testing."
